name: dilipagheda.github.io
description: My Personal Website! This is the first and ninth project as part of Treehouse - FrontEnd Techdegree. It is also further enhanced for Udacity's Frontend developer nanodegree! Yay! It's about customizing a personal online profile by adding graphics, customizing text, and improving the look of a web page using Cascading Style Sheets, the formatting language of the web. As part of ninth project submission towards the end of front end degree, this project was re-written from scratch to act as my personal website.

name: semplice-child
description: A wordpress child theme for orignal theme called Semplice. This child theme implements custom blog - Home page and blog - details page. Design is inspired by surveygizmo.

name: travelplanner-js
description: This is the 5th & a capstone project as part of Udacity front end web developer nanodegree. It is about creating a travel planner app using multiple APIs. Node/Express server acts as a middleware to protect the api keys and interacts with multiple downstream APIs to fetch data about location, image, weather info and country facts

name: flashcards
description: This repo is about hosting various implementation of a project called flashcards. The project has a purpose to help students to prepare for exams via creating flashcards and quizzing themselves. User can create and hold multiple decks of different cards. Currently, this project is implemented using react native, .NET core MVC, react single page app with .NET core MVC Web API as a backend.

name: frontend-dilip-18-2020
description: Math Fun in React! Unit tests in Mocha and Chai.

name: data-table-react
description: A small application developed in React using Hooks and React data grid. It demonstrates how to use react data grid along with redux and hooks. It is written in typescript.

name: countries-react-app
description: A react app to interact with the Rest Countries API and shows country information. Built with React hooks and material UI.

name: marvel-heroes-app
description: A React App that enables a user to navigate through marvel comic characters using Marvel API. The app is built with React 16.8 version with Hooks.

name: serverless-expense-tracker
description: This is a Capstone project as part of AWS Cloud Developer nanodegree from Udacity. It is about building an expense tracker with serverless backend and React client.

name: serverless-app
description: This is the 4th project as part of Udacity Cloud Developer nanodegree. It is about creating a serverless app using AWS Lambda, API Gateway and DynamoDB.

name: udagram
description: This is the 3rd project as part of the Udacity AWS cloud developer nanodegree program. It is about converting the monolith application to microservices, setting up CI/CD with Travis CI, dockerize the modules and then finally deploying it on AWS EKS

name: image-filter-nodejs
description: A node server that processes images using Jimp library. This project was developed as part of Udacity AWS nanodegree program and was deployed to AWS using Elastic beanstalk and tested using Postman.

name: dinosaurs-js
description: This is the 1st project as part of Udacity Intermediate JS Nanodegree. Developed from scratch according to project rubric. It is about creating a Dinosaurs Infogram which compares the human data with predefined dinosaurs and displays in a nice grid format.

name: mars-dashboard
description: This is the 2nd project as part of Udacity Intermediate JavaScript nanodegree. It is about creating a mars dashboard using NASA API using SPA style approach with only plain javascript.

name: full_stack_app_with_react_and_a_rest_api-v1
description: This is the 10th (and final) Project as part of Treehouse Fullstack JavaScript Techdegree. It is about creating a React application that interacts with the School database REST API created in Project 9. The full stack application provides a way to administer a school database.

name: evaluate-news-nlp
description: This is the 4th project as part of Udacity Fronend  Nanodegree 2020. It is about creating a web application that allows user to run Natural language processing (NLP) on articles or blogs found on other websites. for NLP, it uses an API called MeaningCloud. The project's main purpose though is to practice webpack setup from scratch and create build configs for dev and prod environments.

name: weather-journal-js
description: This is the 3rd Project as part of Udacity Frontend developer nanodegree program. It is about using plain JavaScript on both client side and server side to create a weather journal for an user. It uses node.js and express framework on server side to fetch data from weather API.

name: oc-p3-products-admin-module
description: This is 3rd Project as part of OpenclassRooms - Backend .NET diploma path. It is about creating Admin module of shopping cart application to manage products. Features include ability to manage products by logging in as Admin user, Unit tests, Integration tests and database integration using SQL Server.

name: oc-p2-shopping-app
description: This project is a shopping cart app built with ASP .NET Core MVC. It is a 2nd project as part of the OpenClassrooms - Backend developer path - .Net Core. This project was given with all required unit tests. The unit tests were failing initially and goal was to implement the functionality so that unit tests will pass.

name: oc-p1-onlineresume-react
description: This is the 1st Project at OpenClassRooms - Backend .Net Core Path. It is about creating an online resume in React using functional components. Mockup design was provided by the UX team and idea was to implement it in React and style it using SAAS so that the implementation matches the mock up exactly.

name: rest_api-mongo-v1
description: This is the 9th Project as part of Treehouse Fullstack JavaScript Techdegree. It is about creating an API for managing a school database. The API will provide a way for users to administer a school database containing information about courses: users can interact with the database by retrieving a list of courses, as well as adding, updating and deleting courses in the database.

name: oc-p5-carhub
description: This is the 5th Project as part of Openclassroom's .NET Backend Developer Path. It is about building a web application for a company called Car Hub. This company's main business is to buy old car, repair it and then resell. This web application allows the company to manage their car inventory and let their customer's view what cards they have got at moment.

name: udaciracer
description: This is the 3rd Project as part of Udacity's Intermediate JavaScript nanodegree. It is about creating a simulation game of car racing. It allows user to choose track and a racer based on different characteristics. The aim of this project is to practice writing async javascript code with promises, fetch api and async/await.

name: landing-page
description: This is the 2nd project as part of Udacity - Frontend Developer Nanodegree 2020. It is about creating an interactive and dynamic landing page that will add content and interactivity at run time using JavaScript.

name: blog-template
description: This is the 1st project as part of Udacity Frontend Nanodegree 2020. It is about creating a static web template for a simple Blog site. It consists of a blog home page and a blog details page along with navigation bar and a footer

name: oc-p7-poseidon
description: This is the 7th project as part of Openclassroom's Backend .NET developer path. It is about creating a .Net Core API with Entity framework and SQL Server database, Authentication and authorisation and also a front end web application using MVC.

name: oc-p6-bugtracker
description: This is the 6th Project as part of Openclassroom's Backend .NET Path. It is about creating a backend side of a BugTracker application. It involves creating code-first migration using entity framework, creation of stored procedures in SQL server to retrieve data and writing repository class as an interface to the database for front end client. It also involves writing integration tests to ensure that data access logic works as intended.

name: oc-p4-groupomania
description: This is the 4th project as part of the Openclassroom's Backend .NET developer path. It is about creating a solution for a company called Groupomania. The solution replicates the popular Groupon website.

name: MovieWatchList
description: This is an app about managing your watch list for movies that you love to watch in your downtime! It is built with ASP .NET MVC, SQL Server, Entity Framework and Razor Views. It has full user authentication using standard Identity classes.

name: react-gallary-app
description: This is the 7th project for Treehouse Fullstack Javascript Techdegree. It is about creating an interactive image gallary using Flicker API. It uses react components, react routes and fetch API.

name: todoey_apps
description: This repo hosts implementations of Todoey project idea using variety of technologies. Todoey is basically a todolist app to keep track of all your tasks. It is simple, elegant and provides enough features to implement and challenges to overcome while trying to build.

name: confusion-react
description: This is the project developed as part of Coursera's React track under Full-Stack Specialisation of MERN stack

name: reactnd-project-readable
description: Starting server code for ReactND Readable Project

name: Protractor-Cucumber
description: This project contains protractor tests to automate testing of websites. It uses a BDD approach using Cucumber, Gherkin syntax and Page object pattern.

name: conFusion
description: This is the Project built using Bootstrap as part of a Full stack Web Development (Frontend Frameworks) specialisation offered by Hongkong University of Science & Technology through Coursera.

name: sql_library_manager-v1
description: This is the 8th Project as part of Treehouse's Fullstack JS Techdegree. It is a web application that includes pages to list, add, update, and delete books. HTML designs and an existing SQLite database are provided for this project.

name: static_node_and_express_site-v1
description: This is the 6th Project as part of Full stack JavaScript Techdegree for Treehouse. It is about using node.js, express, pug and Json data to create a beautiful portfolio website.

name: FlashChat-Flutter
description: This is the last project as part of Flutter Coding bootcamp from London Appbrewery. This project is about building a Chat application using Flutter for both iOS and Android using Firebase.

name: clima-flutter
description: This project is a weather app implemented in Flutter using Open Weather API. This app was developed as part of London Appbrewery coding bootcamp on Flutter. This app has features like multi-screen data communication, making API call, error handling and use of alerts.

name: bitcoin-flutter
description: This Flutter project is about fetching different crypto-currency prices in various currencies. User can select a currency using iOS picker or Android dropdown depending upon which device the app is run on. It also uses http package to fetch data from an API. This project is developed as part of London Appbrewery coding bootcamp.

name: bmi-calculator-flutter
description: My First Project in Flutter!! It is a BMI (Body Mass Index) calculator inspired by the beautiful design from Dribble. It is developed as part of my coding bootcamp from London Appbrewery. This app is developed in Flutter which builds for both iOS and Android. It has a rich set of Widgets and multi-screen functionality.

name: PopularMovies
description: An app that shows popular movies using MoviesDB API. It uses LoaderManager pattern, Retrofit library and handles rotation of the device by saving state. It was built as one of the project for Android developer nanodegree for Udacity.

name: restaurant-review
description: This is the 5th Project as part of Udacity's Frontend developer Nanodegree Program. It is about converting somewhat existing app into fully responsive, mobile ready app that has offline caching using service workers and is also accessibile to screen readers

name: sports-store
description: This is a customized Sports Store Project based on Adam Freeman's book on ASP.Net MVC 4. I built this project for understanding MVC architecture pattern in C#.NET platform and also to write unit tests for it.

name: CompareSolution
description: This is a small coding exercise and code challenge done for the purpose of practising unit testing in C# and also as part of interview process at tech company in Sydney. The main code is a Compare utility solution for which I wrote full set of unit tests.

name: Todoey
description: A todo list app written for iOS using Swift.

name: Quiz
description: A simple Quiz app with loads of potential to add extra features. I developed this to practice more Android and Java.

name: mobile-first-responsive-layout
description: This is the project 2 of Treehouse Frontend Techdegree. It's about creating a mobile first responsive layout from scratch without using any frameworks. It caters for mobile, tablet and desktop. It is implemented in HTML and CSS based on the design mocks up provided by Treehouse.

name: online_registration_form
description: This is the 3rd project for TreeHouse FrontEnd Techdegree. It's about building the online registration form based on design mock ups.

name: style_guide_v4
description: This is the 4th Project for Treehouse FrontEnd nanodegree. It is about achieving a CSS style for a web page using SAAS based on the design mocks-ups provided.

name: photo_gallery_v4
description: This is the 5th Project for Treehouse Front-End Techdegree! Its an interactive photo gallary with search and lightbox functionality. This project is meant to provide practice for jQuery plugins, JavaScript and lot of CSS!

name: web_app_dashboard_v3.1
description: This is the 7th Project for Treehouse - Frontend Techdegree. Its about creating an interactive analytics page that shows line chart and pie charts using chart.js. It also has SVG icons, Grid layout and animations.

name: employee_directory_v1
description: This is the 8th Project for Treehouse FrontEnd Techdegree. It's about using a FetchAPI to make a network call to RandomAPI to retrieve JSON data of random people and display them on a page using HTML, CSS and Javascript as an employee directory. It also has an overlay popup that displays more information for a given employee.

name: list_pagination_and_filtering-v1
description: This is the 2nd project for Treehouse Full Stack JavaScript Techdegree. It is about writing unobtrusive javascript to achieve pagination and search functionality for better user experience. User can navigate back and forth on different pages and can also search and update pagination based on new search result.

name: game_show_app_v1.2
description: This project is done as part of Treehouse Front-End and Full stack JS Techdegree. Initially it was implemented as pure function based and later was refactored using ES6 OOP style using classes. Its about creating a word game where player can guess a letter in the random word. Player has upto 5 lives and game is lost if all 5 lives are used. If player guesses all letters of the word within 5 lives then player wins!

name: memory-game
description: This is the project done as part of Udacity's FrontEnd Developer Nanodegree Program. It is an interactive card game where user has to find a pair of cards that matches. this game keeps total number of moves, star rating and lots of cool animations.

name: a_random_quote_generator-v1
description: This is the 1st project for Treehouse Full Stack JavaScript techdegree program. It is about writing plain java script to generate a random quote, category, source, year and citation and display it beautifully on the page. It uses JSON object to define various attributes of a quote object. It also has features like new quote every 20 seconds and changing background color and text color for every new quote to provide more engaging user experience.

name: interactive-form-v1
description: This is the 3rd Project for Treehouse Full Stack JavaScript Techdegree. It is about creating an interactive form by using jQuery and adding form validations , interactive form elements based on other form elements and error handling via meaningful and dynamic error messages.

name: arcade-game
description: This is the 3rd Project as part of Udacity's Frontend developer nanodegree. It is about creating an Arcade Game using Object oriented Javascript. The project is used as a means to practice the skill of writing Objects Oriented JS.

name: BakingRecipe
description: Let's bake some dessert! A Baking Recipe app for android. I built this app from scratch as one of the project for Udacity Android developer Nanodegree.

name: PopularMovies2
description: This app is built on top of PopularMovies repo. It shows popular movies, trailers and reviews with extra features to save favourite movies locally using the MoviesDB public API. It supports both portrait and landscape modes. It uses Android architecture components such as LiveData, ViewModel and Room database. I built this project from scratch as part of Udacity Android developer nanodegree program.

name: Miwok
description: Learn the Miwok Language using this android app! This app is built as part of Udacity Basic Nanodegree program.

name: Calculator
description: This is the simple calculator app for Android written in Java. It supports adaptive layouts for portrait and landscape modes using Constraint Layouts. It also preserves the state by saving it to the bundle during screen config change.

name: feedreader-jasmine
description: This is the 4th Project as part of Udacity Frontend developer nanodegree. It's about developing unit test suite for the feed reader application. It uses the popular JavaScript framework, Jasmine, for unit tests.

name: fairfax-candidate-testing-challenge-android
description: A news app for Android. It was a coding challenge by Fairfax Media to write automated UI tests using Espresso framework for Android.

name: fairfax-candidate-testing-challenge-ios
description: A sample news app in iOS - Swift. It was a coding challenge by Fairfax Media to write automated UI tests using XCTest framework in Swift.

name: sandwich_club
description: An app that shows interesting details about sandwiches around the world! It's a sandwiches wikipedia. It is built as the first project for Android developer nanodegree.

name: Flash-Chat-iOS11
description: A chat application written using Firebase for iOS in Swift.

name: Bitcoin-Ticker-iOS11
description: A simple currency converter from a chosen currency to Bitcoin. Written for iOS in Swift.

name: Clima-iOS11
description: A simple weather app written for iOS in Swift using open weather API.
